  "texts": [
    "Pedestrian Detection DatasetsThe MIT-CBCL Pedestrian Database is an early public pedestrian database [84].",
    "The database consists of a 90-minute video with 520 frames, of which 420 frames are divided into a training set, and 100 frames are divided into a test set.",
    "The database contains a total of 924 pedestrian images in ppm format with an aspect ratio of 64x128.",
    "The distance from the shoulder to the foot is about 80 pixels.",
    "However, the database contains only two views, front and back, and lacks negative samples.In addition, it does not distinguish between training and test sets."
  ],
